1
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:23,149
<i>That's exactly why I'm more nervous</i>

2
00:00:23,232 --> 00:00:24,400
<i>about what we're about to do.</i>

3
00:00:24,483 --> 00:00:27,403
<i>No matter what happens,</i>
<i>we still meet at our spot at the Ruins.</i>

4
00:00:27,486 --> 00:00:29,613
<i>We inspected city surveillance footage.</i>

5
00:00:29,697 --> 00:00:31,365
<i>You were with Yana Kassir.</i>

6
00:00:31,449 --> 00:00:33,659
<i>You make yourself</i>
<i>a part of all her crimes.</i>

7
00:00:33,743 --> 00:00:36,245
<i>Please, sir, you have to find Yana.</i>
<i>Or whatever her name is.</i>

8
00:00:36,328 --> 00:00:37,204
<i>We did already.</i>

9
00:00:37,288 --> 00:00:38,998
<i>She was found dead in Sidi Kaouki.</i>

10
00:00:39,081 --> 00:00:41,917
Crisanto, since your name
was included in a Royal Pardon,

11
00:00:42,001 --> 00:00:42,835
<i>that's why you're being released.</i>

12
00:00:42,918 --> 00:00:44,044
I left the country with nothing.

13
00:00:44,128 --> 00:00:45,671
<i>Now, I've come home, still with nothing.</i>

14
00:00:45,755 --> 00:00:47,590
Son, get settled first.

15
00:00:47,673 --> 00:00:51,135
I know for sure you'll get a nice job.

16
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:52,052
<i>But if I hadn't gotten help right away,</i>

17
00:00:52,136 --> 00:00:53,387
<i>things would've probably been worse.</i>

18
00:00:53,471 --> 00:00:54,889
Contact me.
There's a job offer waiting for you.

19
00:00:54,972 --> 00:00:57,516
<i>Actually, there will be</i>
<i>a birthday party at home soon.</i>

20
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,517
<i>You'll be there, okay?</i>

21
00:00:59,852 --> 00:01:00,811
Yana.

22
00:01:38,849 --> 00:01:40,017
Excuse me?

23
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:42,686
Yana Kassir.

24
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:44,188
Yana who?

25
00:01:45,898 --> 00:01:47,525
I think you have the wrong person.

26
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:49,860
Steven, can you give me
another glass, please?

27
00:01:49,944 --> 00:01:51,028
Yes, sir.

28
00:01:51,529 --> 00:01:52,488
Love?

29
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,406
- Teo.
- Boss.

30
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:55,574
I see you've met my wife.

31
00:01:56,617 --> 00:01:58,702
Love, this is Teo,

32
00:01:58,786 --> 00:02:00,329
the guy who saved my life.

33
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:02,665
Oh. So, you're Teo?

34
00:02:03,499 --> 00:02:05,292
Thank you for saving my husband's life.

35
00:02:06,293 --> 00:02:07,962
So, are you ready to work?

36
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:10,506
Yes, sir. I've brought
my clearance and my resume.

37
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:11,841
Nice.

38
00:02:11,924 --> 00:02:14,593
Thank you. Uh, Steven, this is Teo.

39
00:02:14,677 --> 00:02:15,845
I offered him a job.

40
00:02:15,928 --> 00:02:19,390
He's a mechanic,
and he can also be my driver.

41
00:02:19,849 --> 00:02:21,642
- And he also does maintenance, right?
- Wow.

42
00:02:21,725 --> 00:02:23,269
- All-around?
- Yes, sir.

43
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:25,479
I give competitive rates
to all my staff and household.

44
00:02:25,563 --> 00:02:27,439
It's nice to meet you, Teo.

45
00:02:27,523 --> 00:02:29,441
And love,
Mom's looking for us.

46
00:02:29,525 --> 00:02:30,734
- Let's go.
- Oh, okay.

47
00:02:30,818 --> 00:02:32,403
Teo, enjoy the party.

48
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:33,612
Sir.

49
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:42,621
Lino, I'd like you to meet
my daughter-in-law, Gem.

50
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:45,416
Gem, this is Lino, Lino del Rosario.

51
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:48,961
He's been asking about
investing in our US branch.

52
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:51,171
But you're supposed
to be overseeing it, right?

53
00:02:51,255 --> 00:02:54,008
Mom, that's what we want
to discuss with you.

54
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:55,885
Uh, Lino,
would you excuse us, please?

55
00:02:55,968 --> 00:02:57,678
- Okay.
Get some drinks over there.

56
00:02:57,761 --> 00:02:58,888
Thank you.

57
00:03:01,891 --> 00:03:06,145
Rica, can you please tell the chef
to serve the food within 15 minutes?

58
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:11,108
Mom, Dad, we're planning
on having kids soon.

59
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:14,904
Oh. That's going to make me
a grandmother so soon.

60
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:19,992
And it's also the reason why
we've been planning to go to the US.

61
00:03:20,409 --> 00:03:21,285
Permanently.

62
00:03:21,994 --> 00:03:23,120
We?

63
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:25,581
Permanently?

64
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:27,583
And when is this happening?

65
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:28,959
Within the year.

66
00:03:29,043 --> 00:03:30,502
That's good.

67
00:03:30,586 --> 00:03:31,795
Move out already.

68
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:33,505
Live your own life.

69
00:03:33,589 --> 00:03:34,632


70
00:03:35,841 --> 00:03:38,260
It's Gem's birthday,
but I'm the one surprised.

71
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:42,181
Gem, we're still supposed
to be launching our new designs, right?

72
00:03:42,264 --> 00:03:45,309
- I know, Mom.
Stop. Enough talk.

73
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:48,687
What's this family conference
in the middle of the party?

74
00:03:48,771 --> 00:03:51,649
It's good to see
you're enjoying yourself, Gem.

75
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:54,652
Too bad
Jorge and Adriana couldn't make it.

76
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:56,904
I know,
but we didn't want to risk it.

77
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:59,740
We still don't have
the go signal from the doctor,

78
00:03:59,823 --> 00:04:00,866
and she's still feeling weak.

79
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:04,161
You mean your mother
went through all that by herself?

80
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:07,790
And you weren't there by her side
to give her support?

81
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:10,584
With or without me, she's a strong woman.

82
00:04:10,668 --> 00:04:15,130

She's not overly clingy or dependent.

83
00:04:15,214 --> 00:04:18,217
If her child is happy, she's happy.

84
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,010
- Great mom.
Yeah.

85
00:04:20,094 --> 00:04:21,512
Runs in the family.

86
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:23,263
That's why Gem is great too.

87
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:25,015
But...

88
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:28,102
I'm so happy that I get to celebrate
my birthday with you guys.

89
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:32,523
Love, Dad, Mom, Raya,

90
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:33,607
you're my family.

91
00:04:34,191 --> 00:04:38,612
Well, family is family,
even if we're not perfect.

92
00:04:38,696 --> 00:04:40,823

Oh, speak for yourself, Divino.

93
00:04:40,906 --> 00:04:44,243
I am perfect, and so are my children.

94
00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:45,536
Aww!

95
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:47,162
Thanks, Mom.

96
00:04:47,705 --> 00:04:49,707
But you don't need to patronize us.

97
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,418
I don't need to patronize you,
but you know...

98
00:04:53,335 --> 00:04:56,338
patronizing is only for people

99
00:04:56,422 --> 00:04:58,257

who want something in return.

100
00:04:58,841 --> 00:05:03,137
I can't speak
for Ace being... perfect.

101
00:05:03,721 --> 00:05:05,764
Congratulations,
you won the case,

102
00:05:05,848 --> 00:05:08,600
but we all know
perfectly well that Guevarra is guilty.

103
00:05:08,684 --> 00:05:10,769

Even suspects still have rights.

104
00:05:10,853 --> 00:05:12,855
Everyone's innocent
until proven guilty, Dad.

105
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:15,357

There's nothing more true than that.

106
00:05:15,441 --> 00:05:18,152
Defend the victim
who needs justice,

107
00:05:18,235 --> 00:05:20,571

not the accused who still get away.

108
00:05:20,654 --> 00:05:22,156
They can get away
because it can be gotten around.

109
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:23,615

That means there's this one percent

110
00:05:23,699 --> 00:05:25,075
out of one hundred percent probability--

111
00:05:25,159 --> 00:05:27,286
Justice is black and white, not gray.

112
00:05:27,369 --> 00:05:29,705
But somewhere around those gray areas,
there are circumstances that--

113
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:34,293
The reason I could retire
as a judge with a clean reputation

114
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:36,003

is because I recognize black and white.

115
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:37,087


116
00:05:37,171 --> 00:05:38,964

And that's the path you should follow.

117
00:05:39,048 --> 00:05:42,092
I don't think
Ace wants to be a judge, Dad.

118
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,845
He's not judgmental.

119
00:05:46,722 --> 00:05:50,184
I love my family,
my witty daughter.

120
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:52,269
Oh, Mama loves you.

121
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:53,854
- I love you, Mom.
And of course,

122
00:05:53,937 --> 00:05:56,315
my very handsome son.

123
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:58,525
Who's that guy?

124
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:02,571
I thought I saw him
roaming around the party.

125
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:05,491
Mom, come with me.
Everyone, join me, please.

126
00:06:06,158 --> 00:06:07,242
Teo!

127
00:06:09,912 --> 00:06:13,332
I'd like you to meet my beautiful mother,
Katarina Verona.

128
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:16,293
My father, retired judge, Divino Verona.

129
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,213
My lovely sister, Raya.
And of course,

130
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:21,381
you've met my amazing wife, Gem.

131
00:06:21,465 --> 00:06:25,677
Everybody, this is Teo Crisanto,
the guy who saved my life.

132
00:06:26,804 --> 00:06:28,514
- Good evening.
Oh, so that's you.

133
00:06:28,597 --> 00:06:30,390
Thank you for saving my son.

134
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:35,562
Ace, don't you think you should give him
some kind of a thank-you?

135
00:06:35,646 --> 00:06:36,605
I already did.

136
00:06:37,106 --> 00:06:39,191
I gave him a job,
and he's gonna start working for me.

137
00:06:39,817 --> 00:06:42,111

I saw your name in the police report.

138
00:06:42,861 --> 00:06:44,446
Mateo Crisanto, right?

139
00:06:44,530 --> 00:06:45,489
Yes, sir.

140
00:06:45,572 --> 00:06:46,824
Teo is my nickname.

141
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:48,158
Weren't you scared?

142
00:06:48,242 --> 00:06:49,493
There were three of them.

143
00:06:49,576 --> 00:06:51,078

You could've just walked away.

144
00:06:51,662 --> 00:06:54,998
It would've weighed heavier
on me if I turned my back on a situation

145
00:06:55,082 --> 00:06:56,834
where I knew I could help.

146
00:06:57,709 --> 00:07:01,088
You weren't afraid of getting hurt
for someone else?

147
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:03,090
It was already three against one
when I got there.

148
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:04,508
That wasn't fair.

149
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:07,344

I just spoke to General Garcia

150
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:13,100
and he said that two of the three men
who attacked Ace are already in custody,

151
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:15,227
and now they're in pursuit
of the third one.

152
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:17,229
Mom, that's good to hear.

153
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:19,773
Love, I think it's time
to blow your birthday cake.

154
00:07:19,857 --> 00:07:20,983
Shall we?

155
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:21,942
- Yeah.
Let's go, everyone.

156
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:25,028
Let's all gather together
and go to the pool area, everyone.

157
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:28,574
Sir.

158
00:07:30,701 --> 00:07:34,663
No one hurts a Verona
without facing the consequences.

159
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:37,916
If you stand
with the Veronas, you'll be safe for life.

160
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,543
So choose wisely.

161
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:43,213
Yes, sir.

162
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,720
<i>What do you think about Teo, love?</i>

163
00:07:50,304 --> 00:07:51,722
I don't know. He's okay.

164
00:07:52,306 --> 00:07:54,391
I just found it kind of weird earlier

165
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:57,477
because he was calling me
by a different name.

166
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:58,937
I can't remember.

167
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:02,191
Well, you get that a lot.

168
00:08:03,901 --> 00:08:07,112
Remember in Italy
when people approached you?

169
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:10,407
I know. So weird.

170
00:08:12,659 --> 00:08:14,786
Doppelgangers.

171
00:08:15,245 --> 00:08:16,705
Well, they say...

172
00:08:18,957 --> 00:08:20,292
every person is likely to have

173
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:22,544
six or seven doppelgangers
in their lifetime.

174
00:08:22,628 --> 00:08:23,629
Hmm.

175
00:08:23,712 --> 00:08:24,546
But don't worry.

176
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:26,506
I don't sense anything bad about him.

177
00:08:27,925 --> 00:08:29,801
Before he does anything stupid,

178
00:08:29,885 --> 00:08:31,178
I'll get ahead of it.

179
00:08:31,762 --> 00:08:32,596
Good.

180
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:36,410
Boss.

181
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:40,706
Is there someone here
from Santa Reina that I can talk to?

182
00:09:40,789 --> 00:09:42,374
I just need some records.

183
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:43,792
This place has been closed
for a long time, sir.

184
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:48,880
You can e-mail
santareinademanila.ph.mla.

185
00:09:48,964 --> 00:09:50,090
Maybe someone will reply.

186
00:09:51,216 --> 00:09:52,050
Thanks, boss.

187
00:09:52,843 --> 00:09:55,095


188
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:12,279
Teo, I owe you <i>turon </i>tomorrow.

189
00:10:12,362 --> 00:10:14,031
Two for double luck.

190
00:10:14,114 --> 00:10:15,532
Wow, thanks.

191
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,868
Once I pay off our debts,

192
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:20,037
I'll start saving for your tuition.

193
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,248
Then we'll expand our car wash.

194
00:10:23,999 --> 00:10:25,167
One step at a time.

195
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,794
We'll get there.

196
00:10:27,878 --> 00:10:29,338
- Son.
- Pa.

197
00:10:29,421 --> 00:10:31,548
I told you, take it slow.

198
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:33,300
Yes, Pa.

199
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:34,885
Wait, what about me?

200
00:10:35,302 --> 00:10:36,553
Where's my treat?

201
00:10:37,262 --> 00:10:39,389
- I'll just take one.
- Wow, Ronnie!

202
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:40,682
You're something else!

203
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:45,520
So where are you working, Teo?

204
00:10:46,021 --> 00:10:47,981
At Attorney Ace Verona's.

205
00:10:48,065 --> 00:10:48,982
Huh?

206
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,485
Attorney Ace Verona?

207
00:10:52,027 --> 00:10:53,779
Teo, he's the one
who gave me a scholarship.

208
00:10:53,862 --> 00:10:54,988
That's how I got to study.

209
00:10:55,072 --> 00:10:57,699
And he's Katarina Verona's son.

210
00:10:57,783 --> 00:11:00,494
"The Dame of Diamonds."

211
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:01,953
Have you applied already, Larajean?

212
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:04,873
Oh, come on.

213
00:11:04,956 --> 00:11:08,377
I bet a hundred,
you're just going to follow Teo there.

214
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:09,628
- A hundred?
- Yeah!

215
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:11,546
A hundred. Here.

216
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:14,132
You're good, huh?

217
00:11:14,216 --> 00:11:16,009
Of course, wherever Teo goes, I go.

218
00:11:17,928 --> 00:11:20,847
Just kidding. I need this money.

219
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:23,308
Not there.

220
00:11:24,142 --> 00:11:26,144
- Why not?
- I'm serious, Larajean.

221
00:11:26,895 --> 00:11:29,064
Not there.

222
00:11:29,815 --> 00:11:31,358
Let's just close up.

223
00:11:31,441 --> 00:11:33,318
- Hello, Jepoy.
- You close the gate.

224
00:11:33,402 --> 00:11:35,028
Teo, long time.

225
00:11:35,112 --> 00:11:36,446
I got your message.

226
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:38,323
Good thing you're back in the Philippines.

227
00:11:38,407 --> 00:11:40,951
Yeah, I got pardoned.

228
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:42,285
That's good to hear.

229
00:11:42,369 --> 00:11:43,495
How are things?

230
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:45,539
Just starting over.

231
00:11:46,331 --> 00:11:47,833
Jepoy, I need a favor.

232
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,836
<i>Can you get a death certificate</i>
<i>or police report?</i>

233
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:53,380
Anything that proves Yana is really dead.

234
00:11:53,463 --> 00:11:55,841
<i>Cause of death, autopsy,</i>

235
00:11:55,924 --> 00:11:57,384
photos, anything.

236
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:59,261
Isn't she that troublesome girl
from before?

237
00:11:59,761 --> 00:12:01,179
Why? What for?

238
00:12:01,263 --> 00:12:02,848
I just need it.

239
00:12:02,931 --> 00:12:05,016
All right, I'll try on my day off.

240
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,435
Thanks, bro.

241
00:12:06,518 --> 00:12:07,644
<i>All right.</i>

242
00:12:10,188 --> 00:12:11,106
Yana?

243
00:12:12,149 --> 00:12:13,191
Police report?

244
00:12:13,275 --> 00:12:14,818
Death certificate?

245
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,285
- Alvin.
- Yes?

246
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:24,703
Take him upstairs.

247
00:12:34,004 --> 00:12:35,547
Sir, good morning.

248
00:12:36,131 --> 00:12:38,091
Next time, don't drop people off here.

249
00:12:38,175 --> 00:12:39,634
They should be at the garage.

250
00:12:39,718 --> 00:12:40,802
Sorry, sir.

251
00:12:40,886 --> 00:12:41,970
Come on.

252
00:12:43,013 --> 00:12:44,598
This is the garage.

253
00:12:45,307 --> 00:12:47,934
All of our bosses' cars are parked here.

254
00:12:48,018 --> 00:12:50,479
You'll maintain all of them daily.

255
00:12:50,562 --> 00:12:54,065
Everything should be in running condition.

256
00:12:54,149 --> 00:12:56,443
Don't touch them carelessly.

257
00:12:56,526 --> 00:12:58,862
Even a lifetime of work
wouldn't be enough to pay for them.

258
00:12:58,945 --> 00:12:59,779
Sorry, sir.

259
00:12:59,863 --> 00:13:02,199
If there's a problem with the pool,

260
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:04,701
you can pass here.
The pump room is there.

261
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:06,661
That leads to the service area.

262
00:13:06,745 --> 00:13:10,290
- That's Gani, our gardener.
- Hello.

263
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:13,585
This is Mabel, our live-in helper.

264
00:13:13,668 --> 00:13:15,420
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

265
00:13:15,504 --> 00:13:18,089
This is Lenlen,
also a live-in cleaner.

266
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:19,549
Hello.

267
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:21,676
This is the pantry.

268
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:23,762
You can eat here.

269
00:13:24,554 --> 00:13:26,264
Benefits are good here.

270
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:30,393
Free food, Wi-Fi, good management.

271
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:32,562
That's why people stay long
with the Verona family.

272
00:13:32,646 --> 00:13:34,648
You can leave your things here.

273
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,526
And this is Miss Rica.

274
00:13:37,609 --> 00:13:38,818
Hello.

275
00:13:38,902 --> 00:13:40,445
These are your uniforms.

276
00:13:40,529 --> 00:13:43,615
For drivers, maintenance, and staff.

277
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:48,537
There are CCTV cameras
all over the property.

278
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:49,579
Like those.

279
00:13:49,663 --> 00:13:51,665
There's also roving security.

280
00:13:51,748 --> 00:13:54,292
No CCTV inside the house,
Sir Ace doesn't want that.

281
00:13:54,376 --> 00:13:57,671
Only trusted people are allowed inside.

282
00:13:59,089 --> 00:14:00,298
I'll repeat,

283
00:14:01,174 --> 00:14:04,261
unless I call you, you don't go in.

284
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:05,470
Got it?

285
00:14:05,554 --> 00:14:06,638
Got it, sir.

286
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:08,598
Do you know electrical maintenance?

287
00:14:08,682 --> 00:14:10,433
- Yes, sir.
- You know everything, huh?

288
00:14:10,517 --> 00:14:11,601
All right.

289
00:14:11,685 --> 00:14:14,771
Fix the lamp in Ma'am Raya's room.

290
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:18,441
The tools are in the pump room.

291
00:14:18,525 --> 00:14:20,819
I'll have Mabel accompany you inside.

292
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:22,404
Yes.

293
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:24,155
There's a big discount.

294
00:14:27,576 --> 00:14:32,122
Mom said
you're one of her most loyal clients.

295
00:14:32,664 --> 00:14:34,291
We won't disappoint you.

296
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:36,543
Understood.

297
00:14:37,085 --> 00:14:39,462
Yes, thank you.

298
00:14:39,754 --> 00:14:40,589
Bye.

299
00:14:59,149 --> 00:15:00,442
Impressive!

300
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:04,195
- That was fast.
- This is all set, ma'am.

301
00:15:04,279 --> 00:15:07,032
- All done? Great!
- Mm-hmm.

302
00:15:07,115 --> 00:15:10,619
Do you have a favorite snack?
I can have some cooked for you.

303
00:15:10,702 --> 00:15:12,329
- I'm all right...
- Mabel?

304
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:13,747
What about the master's bedroom?

305
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,624
Well, I did Miss Raya's--

306
00:15:15,707 --> 00:15:17,042
Shouldn't that be done by now?

307
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,585
- Well, I did this fi--
- Go.

308
00:15:18,668 --> 00:15:20,670
- I had this check--
- Go.

309
00:15:20,754 --> 00:15:22,547
- That should've been done earlier.
- Yes, sir.

310
00:15:22,631 --> 00:15:24,215
Teo, what about the task I gave you?

311
00:15:24,299 --> 00:15:25,383
- It's done, sir.
- Sure?

312
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:27,761
- Yes, sir.
- Go back to the staff room.

313
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:29,137
Okay, sir.

314
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:35,518
- Why are you here?
- Are you all right?

315
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:37,103
Ma'am, ma'am.

316
00:15:37,187 --> 00:15:38,897
Sit down first.

317
00:15:41,024 --> 00:15:43,360
Do we have to take you to the hospital?

318
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:46,237
My blood sugar just went down.

319
00:15:46,321 --> 00:15:48,406
Have you taken your medicine yet?
Your insulin?

320
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:51,409
Just oral medicine. No insulin yet.

321
00:15:51,493 --> 00:15:53,620
You and my dad are the same.

322
00:15:54,913 --> 00:15:56,039
He's also diabetic.

323
00:15:56,122 --> 00:15:58,500
Goodness, this illness is so expensive.

324
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,001
You're absolutely right.

325
00:16:00,669 --> 00:16:05,256
I even had to work abroad back then
to afford my father's medicine.

326
00:16:07,092 --> 00:16:08,093
Really?

327
00:16:10,095 --> 00:16:13,139
It's really tough
when your parents have health conditions.

328
00:16:14,516 --> 00:16:16,601
I can totally relate.

329
00:16:17,727 --> 00:16:18,687
Good morning, ma'am.

330
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:20,146
- Good morning, ma'am.
- Good morning, ma'am.

331
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:22,524
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

332
00:16:22,607 --> 00:16:25,068
Which one of your parents is sick?

333
00:16:25,735 --> 00:16:27,779
- My mother.
- Cancer?

334
00:16:27,862 --> 00:16:29,030
No.

335
00:16:29,531 --> 00:16:30,365
Kidney.

336
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:32,325
She's had problems with her kidneys.

337
00:16:32,409 --> 00:16:34,119
That's why she's on dialysis.

338
00:16:35,453 --> 00:16:36,996
I'm sorry.

339
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:40,166
I don't know why I thought of lung cancer.

340
00:16:47,382 --> 00:16:49,592
Well, Rica, how are you doing?

341
00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:50,719
I'm doing fine now, ma'am.

342
00:16:50,802 --> 00:16:53,096
My blood sugar has gone up, ma'am.

343
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:54,764
It runs in the family.

344
00:16:54,848 --> 00:16:56,433
My father went through dialysis as well.

345
00:16:56,766 --> 00:16:59,978
I almost went abroad too, just like Teo.

346
00:17:00,061 --> 00:17:01,771
I wish I hadn't gone abroad.

347
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:03,189
Why not?

348
00:17:03,273 --> 00:17:05,358
I went through hell over there.

349
00:17:05,442 --> 00:17:06,735
I really hit rock bottom.

350
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:09,404
There were a lot of scammers.

351
00:17:10,572 --> 00:17:13,158
And then, a demon destroyed my life.

352
00:17:13,241 --> 00:17:14,659
Like who?

353
00:17:19,122 --> 00:17:20,373
Mabel, you take over for now

354
00:17:20,457 --> 00:17:22,876
- so Rica can get some rest.
- Yes, ma'am.

355
00:17:22,959 --> 00:17:25,253
- The person who ruined my life?
- Mm.

356
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:28,423
I've already put it in the past, ma'am.

357
00:17:29,382 --> 00:17:32,135
I've already buried
all my memories of her.

358
00:17:32,635 --> 00:17:34,637
Karma will catch up
to them eventually.

359
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:38,141
Rica, I told you to rest.

360
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:39,392
All right, ma'am.

361
00:17:42,187 --> 00:17:43,313
Well, as you should.

362
00:17:43,897 --> 00:17:45,356
Are you done
with everything in the garage?

363
00:17:46,816 --> 00:17:48,067
There's still a lot to do, ma'am.

364
00:17:48,151 --> 00:17:49,944
You better get going.

365
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:55,241
All right, ma'am.

366
00:17:56,951 --> 00:17:59,078
Mabel, I'm here to ask you
to restock the milk in the pantry.

367
00:17:59,162 --> 00:18:00,997
We're out of milk, okay?

368
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,208
Oh, there's no milk?
All right, I'll get some.

369
00:18:11,132 --> 00:18:13,384
<i>Even if I try to deny it,</i>

370
00:18:13,468 --> 00:18:15,220
<i>I know it's you, Yana.</i>

371
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:18,306
<i>Something feels off.</i>

372
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:20,099
<i>What I see says otherwise.</i>

373
00:18:20,391 --> 00:18:22,227
<i>I sense something else entirely.</i>

374
00:18:23,353 --> 00:18:25,313
<i>I know you're pretending.</i>

375
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:27,690
<i>You're heartless, Yana.</i>

376
00:18:28,483 --> 00:18:30,527
<i>You ruined my life.</i>

377
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:33,279
<i>You ruined my family's life.</i>

378
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:45,458
<i>It really is Yana, my friend.</i>

379
00:18:45,542 --> 00:18:48,127
It really is her body.
Have you seen what I sent you?

380
00:18:48,211 --> 00:18:50,213
Not yet. I'll check it out.

381
00:19:02,851 --> 00:19:04,018
Jepoy.

382
00:19:04,102 --> 00:19:06,187
<i>That really was her body.</i>

383
00:19:06,271 --> 00:19:07,772
<i>She's dead, Teo.</i>

384
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:10,233
Where were the people with her?

385
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:13,278
There is no news on them.
They're probably dead as well.

386
00:19:13,361 --> 00:19:15,572
Something feels off here, Jepoy.

387
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:18,032
What more proof do you want, Teo?

388
00:19:18,116 --> 00:19:20,493
The police found Yana's body.

389
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:28,585
Look at Gem's designs.

390
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:32,922
So dull, so lifeless, no beauty.

391
00:19:33,006 --> 00:19:35,133
Wanting to execute so much,

392
00:19:35,216 --> 00:19:37,510
and yet, nothing was executed properly.

393
00:19:37,594 --> 00:19:39,304
And that's because I was never consulted.

394
00:19:39,387 --> 00:19:42,599
If you want to criticize Gem,
say it to her!

395
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:44,642
She's not criticizing Gem.

396
00:19:44,726 --> 00:19:45,852
Only her designs.

397
00:19:45,935 --> 00:19:47,312
Thank you, Mr. Interpreter.

398
00:19:47,395 --> 00:19:49,063
So Ace, you're willing to change

399
00:19:49,147 --> 00:19:51,190
the course of your life
because of that woman?

400
00:19:51,274 --> 00:19:54,485
"That woman" is now my wife.

401
00:19:54,569 --> 00:19:56,821
- My legal wife.
- Ha!

402
00:19:56,905 --> 00:19:58,740
That was just a whirlwind romance!

403
00:19:58,823 --> 00:19:59,824
You just got excited!

404
00:19:59,908 --> 00:20:01,576
Three months into the relationship,

405
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:04,537
she toyed with you
until you finally married her.

406
00:20:04,621 --> 00:20:07,165
No one toyed with me, Ma.
It was my own decision.

407
00:20:07,248 --> 00:20:09,208
Yes,
and your decision to leave everything

408
00:20:09,292 --> 00:20:11,419
you've built here just because of her!

409
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:13,838
Yes! Because people change plans and goals
along the way.

410
00:20:13,922 --> 00:20:16,090
She's not a cheap woman
I just picked up off the street.

411
00:20:16,174 --> 00:20:17,717
She's well-educated.

412
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,303
She's beautiful,
comes from a wealthy family,

413
00:20:20,386 --> 00:20:22,138
and she's even using her skills
for your business!

414
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:25,433
Yeah, and you just forced me
to accept her here.

415
00:20:25,516 --> 00:20:27,644
Because she believes
in your business, Ma.

416
00:20:29,187 --> 00:20:31,147
She isn't some beggar,
nor is she a gold digger.

417
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,649
They're already adults.

418
00:20:32,732 --> 00:20:34,233
They can make their own decisions,

419
00:20:34,317 --> 00:20:35,944
and we can't do anything about it.

420
00:20:37,904 --> 00:20:38,905
Splendid.

421
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:40,782
And for you, Ace,

422
00:20:40,865 --> 00:20:42,450
I only have one request.

423
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:46,287
If you're planning
on practicing law in the US,

424
00:20:46,663 --> 00:20:50,541
please, don't take controversial cases.

425
00:20:50,625 --> 00:20:52,251
I've been telling you
for the longest time.

426
00:20:52,335 --> 00:20:54,712
Stay out of the public eye.

427
00:20:54,796 --> 00:20:56,005
But here you are.

428
00:20:56,089 --> 00:20:57,674
Do you want more attention?

429
00:20:59,342 --> 00:21:02,470
Finally, my Zoom meeting is over.

430
00:21:03,638 --> 00:21:05,348
- Love?
- Love.

431
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:06,516
How are you?

432
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:07,934
Good. Are you okay?

433
00:21:09,102 --> 00:21:11,145
Good night, my beloved parents.

434
00:21:11,229 --> 00:21:13,231
Good night, Mama. Good night, Papa.

435
00:21:13,314 --> 00:21:14,899
- See you at home.
- Good night.

436
00:21:19,112 --> 00:21:20,780
<i>I heard</i>
<i>everything you guys talked about.</i>

437
00:21:20,863 --> 00:21:22,365
It's been two years.

438
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:23,866
But your mom still looks at me the same.

439
00:21:23,950 --> 00:21:27,161
As if I'm this cheap tramp
you just picked up in Spain.

440
00:21:27,245 --> 00:21:28,496
Love.

441
00:21:28,579 --> 00:21:30,248
We all know that's not true, okay?

442
00:21:30,331 --> 00:21:32,709
I wonder if the way
she sees me will ever change.

443
00:21:32,792 --> 00:21:33,960
It doesn't matter.

444
00:21:34,669 --> 00:21:37,505
We'll continue with our plans
whether Mama likes it or not.

445
00:21:37,588 --> 00:21:38,923
Got that?

446
00:22:09,954 --> 00:22:11,289
I'm here.

447
00:22:14,792 --> 00:22:16,335
Hold on to me. Hold on to me.

448
00:22:16,419 --> 00:22:18,004
Go to bed first.

449
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:23,259
Slowly.

450
00:22:25,636 --> 00:22:27,346
It's just a power outage.

451
00:22:27,638 --> 00:22:29,307
- It's taking too long.
- Let me check.

452
00:22:29,390 --> 00:22:31,059
No, no! Don't!

453
00:22:31,142 --> 00:22:32,310
I'm just here.

454
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:44,197
There's power all over the house.

455
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:13,226
There seems to be no problem.

456
00:23:36,874 --> 00:23:37,834
Is this what you're looking for, Teo?

457
00:23:41,754 --> 00:23:42,964
I'm sorry.

458
00:23:43,714 --> 00:23:46,050
I thought it was a list of expenses.

459
00:23:47,552 --> 00:23:49,053
If she's dead,

460
00:23:49,846 --> 00:23:51,389
then just forget about her.

461
00:23:51,931 --> 00:23:53,558
Just put it behind you.

462
00:23:53,641 --> 00:23:55,560
I saw her in person, Dad.

463
00:23:57,812 --> 00:23:59,272
She's alive.

464
00:24:00,022 --> 00:24:01,566
She's Gem Verona now.

465
00:24:01,649 --> 00:24:02,733
No...

466
00:24:03,442 --> 00:24:05,778
How... how did that happen?

467
00:24:06,028 --> 00:24:07,113
It might just be a coincidence.

468
00:24:07,196 --> 00:24:09,991
Or maybe she's still scamming people
to this day.

469
00:24:10,074 --> 00:24:13,619
Where did you see her personally?

470
00:24:14,871 --> 00:24:16,747
In the mansion.

471
00:24:16,831 --> 00:24:18,499
She's my boss's wife.

472
00:24:19,876 --> 00:24:22,378
You might be better off getting a new job.

473
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:26,465
If that's the case,
then stay away from her.

474
00:24:26,549 --> 00:24:29,594
If she was a plague,
then she's still a plague now.

475
00:24:29,677 --> 00:24:31,554
- Something bad might happ--
- Dad, with everything

476
00:24:31,637 --> 00:24:34,056
I've been through,
I think I know what I'm doing.

477
00:24:35,266 --> 00:24:36,767
That won't happen again.

478
00:24:38,769 --> 00:24:40,688
She will no longer ruin my life.

479
00:24:42,315 --> 00:24:44,066
This time, her life will be ruined.

480
00:24:53,075 --> 00:24:54,493
Good morning, ma'am.

481
00:24:55,244 --> 00:24:57,330
- Is this the applicant?
- Uh, no, ma'am.

482
00:24:57,413 --> 00:25:01,042
She's Sir Ace and Miss Gem's travel agent.

483
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:03,211
- Good morning, madam.
- Good morning.

484
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:07,298
Steven, can you please ask Mabel
to bring me a cup of coffee?

485
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:08,841
- Yes, ma'am.
- Thank you.

486
00:25:08,925 --> 00:25:10,927
But ma'am, we have applicants

487
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:12,970
scheduled for an interview today.

488
00:25:13,054 --> 00:25:14,972
Is it truly impossible for you
to work without an assistant?

489
00:25:15,056 --> 00:25:18,226
I mean, you might be more stressed.

490
00:25:19,018 --> 00:25:20,102
It's hard to train.

491
00:25:20,186 --> 00:25:24,565
But ma'am, my doctor told me
I really need to avoid stress.

492
00:25:24,649 --> 00:25:26,651
Well then,
if it's about your well-being,

493
00:25:26,734 --> 00:25:30,363
I guess you will have to consider
your resignation.

494
00:25:30,446 --> 00:25:32,907
No, that's not the case, ma'am.

495
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:34,242
I can do it.

496
00:25:34,325 --> 00:25:35,660
Sir, ma'am.

497
00:25:35,743 --> 00:25:38,454
I'm just going to have Teo fix
the broken wiring in your room,

498
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:39,747
so what happened last night
doesn't happen again.

499
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:41,624
Love, I'm just having something fixed.

500
00:25:41,707 --> 00:25:42,625
Is that okay?

501
00:25:43,417 --> 00:25:44,877
Sure. Go ahead.

502
00:25:45,461 --> 00:25:46,629
Teo.

503
00:25:48,005 --> 00:25:50,091
Mr. and Mrs. Verona, good morning.

504
00:25:50,174 --> 00:25:51,384
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

505
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:54,762
Here are your papers and your passports
for your migration.

506
00:25:54,845 --> 00:25:56,097
And I know you're very excited--

507
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:57,181
Approval is already expected

508
00:25:57,265 --> 00:25:59,767
with the amount of ties
we have shown to this country.

509
00:25:59,850 --> 00:26:01,560
Especially when it comes to
how much we are willing

510
00:26:01,644 --> 00:26:04,021
- and able to invest in their country.
- Thank you, Lani.

511
00:26:05,273 --> 00:26:06,607
I've brought the tools, sir.

512
00:26:06,691 --> 00:26:07,984
Good.

513
00:26:11,779 --> 00:26:13,864
- Close the door, okay?
- Got it, sir.

514
00:26:14,949 --> 00:26:16,284
Here.

515
00:26:16,367 --> 00:26:18,911
Check that and these switches.

516
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:20,663
Make sure
that it doesn't smell like it's burning,

517
00:26:20,746 --> 00:26:22,123
and don't let it smoke.

518
00:26:22,206 --> 00:26:23,040
All right, sir.

519
00:26:23,124 --> 00:26:27,753
And here is the progress
of your LA house renovations.

520
00:26:27,837 --> 00:26:29,255
Thank you.

521
00:26:29,338 --> 00:26:32,883
Actually, I want to change
something in the front yard.

522
00:26:32,967 --> 00:26:34,969
You think
we can meet the landscape architect?

523
00:26:35,052 --> 00:26:36,470
Um, not today, love.

524
00:26:36,554 --> 00:26:37,638
I do have a hearing.

525
00:26:37,722 --> 00:26:40,182
Let's schedule this meeting
another time, okay?

526
00:26:40,266 --> 00:26:42,226
- Okay, sir.
- Okay. Thank you.

527
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,894
- This way, ma'am.
- Thank you, madam.

528
00:26:43,978 --> 00:26:46,063
This AC unit keeps tripping
the circuit breaker.

529
00:26:46,147 --> 00:26:47,481
That could be the reason.

530
00:26:48,899 --> 00:26:50,234
All right, sir.

531
00:26:50,318 --> 00:26:51,527
Let's check it out.

532
00:26:57,658 --> 00:27:00,411
Sir, we don't have a ladder.
I didn't bring one with me.

533
00:27:00,494 --> 00:27:02,038
You should've brought one earlier.

534
00:27:02,121 --> 00:27:04,123
- I'll get it, sir.
- Don't bother.

535
00:27:04,206 --> 00:27:05,916
I'll just call Gani.

536
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,209
Gani?

537
00:27:08,753 --> 00:27:09,962
Gani?

538
00:27:10,046 --> 00:27:11,255
Gani?

539
00:27:12,715 --> 00:27:13,716
I'll get it. You stay here.

540
00:27:13,799 --> 00:27:15,134
- Don't leave.
- Okay, sir.

541
00:27:25,353 --> 00:27:28,314
Love, can you...
can you get me a nail cutter?

542
00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:30,274
I have a hangnail.
It's just a small one.

543
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:33,486
I'll get one. Give me a minute.

544
00:27:58,552 --> 00:28:00,513
- Ma'am.
- What are you doing here?

545
00:28:00,596 --> 00:28:02,723
Uh, I'm just checking
the wiring and the appliances.

546
00:28:02,807 --> 00:28:04,600
It's possible a short circuit

547
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:06,477
is what caused
the power outage last night.

548
00:28:15,528 --> 00:28:18,614
Steven, why did you leave Teo here alone?

549
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:21,784
Ma'am, we forgot to bring the ladder in.

550
00:28:21,867 --> 00:28:24,203
There are important things in this room.

551
00:28:24,995 --> 00:28:26,956
My husband and I have personal belongings.

552
00:28:27,039 --> 00:28:29,291
And you, of all people,
should know

553
00:28:29,375 --> 00:28:31,293
that you can't be here alone.

554
00:28:31,544 --> 00:28:34,463
Especially if you're new here.

555
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:41,137
I'm sorry, ma'am. This won't happen again.

556
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:42,263
As it should be.

557
00:28:49,145 --> 00:28:50,229
All of you get out.

558
00:28:50,312 --> 00:28:51,772
I need to get ready.

559
00:28:51,856 --> 00:28:53,691
Just finish that up when I leave.

560
00:28:54,775 --> 00:28:55,943
Yes, ma'am.

561
00:28:56,026 --> 00:28:59,280
Yes, ma'am.

562
00:29:01,991 --> 00:29:04,076
- I'm sorry, ma'am.
- Let's go.

563
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:34,440
Are you going
to your golf tournament in Bangkok?

564
00:29:35,191 --> 00:29:36,609
Of course.

565
00:29:38,402 --> 00:29:42,198
But you know that the jewelry launch
is in two weeks, right?

566
00:29:42,281 --> 00:29:45,743
And Ace's attacker
has not yet been convicted.

567
00:29:45,826 --> 00:29:47,828
- He's in jail.
- But that's not enough.

568
00:29:47,912 --> 00:29:49,038
It is enough.

569
00:29:49,121 --> 00:29:50,664
I'll take care of it when I get back.

570
00:29:50,748 --> 00:29:53,667
What's important is that
the suspects have been identified.

571
00:29:53,751 --> 00:29:56,003
It will go through the proper process.

572
00:29:57,254 --> 00:29:58,839
Why don't you stay?

573
00:29:59,381 --> 00:30:00,382
Come on.

574
00:30:00,466 --> 00:30:02,635
- Let's take a road trip.
- I can't.

575
00:30:02,718 --> 00:30:05,304
I have to attend
that golf tournament in Bangkok.

576
00:30:05,971 --> 00:30:08,349
It's still your decision to leave or not.

577
00:30:08,432 --> 00:30:12,228
Unless you'd rather be
there than here, tell me.

578
00:30:12,311 --> 00:30:13,521
And don't lie.

579
00:30:13,604 --> 00:30:15,064
I've hidden
no secrets from you.

580
00:30:15,147 --> 00:30:18,817
Just because I know everything
doesn't mean I agree with it.

581
00:30:37,878 --> 00:30:39,171
Papa! Mama!

582
00:30:39,255 --> 00:30:40,506
Have you seen Steven?

583
00:30:40,589 --> 00:30:41,924
Why? What's the problem?

584
00:30:42,007 --> 00:30:43,717
My passport is missing.

585
00:30:43,801 --> 00:30:44,843
What?

586
00:30:45,928 --> 00:30:47,012
Steven!

587
00:30:47,638 --> 00:30:48,764
Steven!

588
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:49,974
Yes, Judge?

589
00:30:54,144 --> 00:30:55,271
Are you sure?

590
00:30:55,354 --> 00:30:56,605
Yes, I've checked everywhere.

591
00:30:56,689 --> 00:31:00,276
Last seen... it was here with
Ace's passport, but now, mine is missing.

592
00:31:00,359 --> 00:31:01,860
How about here? Did you check here?

593
00:31:01,944 --> 00:31:03,028
Yes, I checked there.

594
00:31:03,112 --> 00:31:04,697
Then it's supposed to be here.

595
00:31:05,281 --> 00:31:06,490
It's not.

596
00:31:07,283 --> 00:31:08,367
Uh, Ma'am Gem?

597
00:31:08,450 --> 00:31:09,618
Where did that go?

598
00:31:09,702 --> 00:31:11,453
Ma'am, how is that possible?

599
00:31:11,537 --> 00:31:12,371
I don't know. You tell me.

600
00:31:12,454 --> 00:31:13,956
You're the one who brought people in here.

601
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:16,834
You were still here
when we did the inspections.

602
00:31:16,917 --> 00:31:18,419
How's that even possible?

603
00:31:18,836 --> 00:31:20,129
In this house?

604
00:31:20,588 --> 00:31:23,299
Well, maybe you just misplaced it, Gem.

605
00:31:23,382 --> 00:31:24,925
Have you checked your things?

606
00:31:25,009 --> 00:31:25,843
Yes.

607
00:31:25,926 --> 00:31:28,637
Next time,
organize your stuff properly.

608
00:31:28,721 --> 00:31:34,059
We tend to depend on the helpers
for everything, you know.

609
00:31:35,227 --> 00:31:38,063
Maybe it's just there,
and you just misplaced it.

610
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,611
Steven, check everyone.

611
00:31:43,694 --> 00:31:45,112
We need to find it.

612
00:31:45,529 --> 00:31:46,614
Yes, Judge.

613
00:31:48,407 --> 00:31:50,618
Teo, do you have it?

614
00:31:50,701 --> 00:31:52,453
Just give it back, will you?

615
00:31:52,536 --> 00:31:54,455
What would I do with Ma'am's passport?

616
00:31:54,538 --> 00:31:56,540
We left her room together, remember?

617
00:31:57,499 --> 00:31:58,834
That's what confuses me, too.

618
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:01,462
I checked the pantry and your locker,
but it's empty.

619
00:32:01,545 --> 00:32:03,714
- Is this yours?
- Yes, sir. That's mine.

620
00:32:09,053 --> 00:32:11,889
Even if you torture me right here,

621
00:32:11,972 --> 00:32:13,724
I know I didn't do anything wrong.

622
00:32:14,350 --> 00:32:18,437
I wouldn't risk this job
for something like that.

623
00:32:19,146 --> 00:32:20,731
For Ma'am's passport?

624
00:32:21,106 --> 00:32:22,858
And what would I do with it? Sell it?

625
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:24,109
Wait.

626
00:32:24,193 --> 00:32:26,528
Why is only Ma'am Gem's passport missing?

627
00:32:26,612 --> 00:32:29,156
Sir Ace's passport is still here.

628
00:32:29,365 --> 00:32:30,199
Mm.

629
00:32:31,492 --> 00:32:33,452
As he'd always say,

630
00:32:33,535 --> 00:32:36,872
what's the motive behind every situation?

631
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:38,540
An intention.

632
00:32:58,852 --> 00:32:59,895
Drive faster.

633
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:05,609
Drive faster, Teo.

634
00:33:08,570 --> 00:33:09,780
Faster.

635
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:13,325
I said, faster!

636
00:33:13,909 --> 00:33:14,993
Sir, this is dangerous.

637
00:33:15,077 --> 00:33:16,829
Don't stop. I got you.

638
00:33:19,957 --> 00:33:21,959
Yeah!

639
00:33:35,472 --> 00:33:36,724
Don't stop.

640
00:33:36,807 --> 00:33:38,434
Let them chase.

641
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:39,768
Sir, I might get arrested.

642
00:33:39,852 --> 00:33:41,687
Don't you trust me?

643
00:33:46,775 --> 00:33:48,527
- Sir...
- Go faster!

644
00:33:52,823 --> 00:33:53,949
Whoo!

645
00:33:54,950 --> 00:33:56,952
Let them chase us!

646
00:34:10,841 --> 00:34:12,009
Boss.

647
00:34:12,092 --> 00:34:12,926
Sir?

648
00:34:13,844 --> 00:34:16,138
- Boss.
- Attorney, good to see you.

649
00:34:16,221 --> 00:34:17,681
What's going on, sir?

650
00:34:17,765 --> 00:34:20,184
We heard your siren,
so we stopped to take a look.

651
00:34:20,267 --> 00:34:22,102
Overspeeding, sir.

652
00:34:22,186 --> 00:34:23,937
The report is showing 168.

653
00:34:24,021 --> 00:34:25,063
That's dangerous.

654
00:34:25,147 --> 00:34:26,982
I know, I know.

655
00:34:27,441 --> 00:34:29,109
Sorry for the trouble.

656
00:34:29,193 --> 00:34:32,321
By the way, my new driver, Teo Crisanto.

657
00:34:32,404 --> 00:34:33,572
Remember his face.

658
00:34:33,655 --> 00:34:35,073
Yes, sir.

659
00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:37,743
- Tuazon.
- Sir.

660
00:34:37,826 --> 00:34:39,620
- Keep him in mind.
- Yes, sir!

661
00:34:39,703 --> 00:34:41,955
Take care on the road, sir.

662
00:34:42,039 --> 00:34:44,333
And say hi to Judge Verona for me.

663
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:46,376
- I got you.
- Okay, Attorney.

664
00:34:46,460 --> 00:34:48,170
- All right. Let's go.
- All right.

665
00:34:57,429 --> 00:34:58,514
Get out.

666
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:03,310
Why, sir?

667
00:35:04,353 --> 00:35:05,938
Do whatever I tell you to do.

668
00:35:06,522 --> 00:35:08,106
But sir...

669
00:35:11,777 --> 00:35:14,530
I am a lawyer and a Verona.

670
00:35:14,613 --> 00:35:17,282
I can get you in and out of jail
no matter what you do.

671
00:35:17,366 --> 00:35:19,326
If you can't obey my orders,

672
00:35:19,618 --> 00:35:20,744
then you're fired.

673
00:35:21,328 --> 00:35:22,496
Let's go!

674
00:35:25,457 --> 00:35:27,543
Well, what do you think, Gem?

675
00:35:33,382 --> 00:35:36,844
The clarity of the gem
is not very transparent.

676
00:35:37,427 --> 00:35:39,054
Underneath the grand design,

677
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:41,306
it has many imperfections and flaws.

678
00:35:42,349 --> 00:35:44,601
As if it hides some evil within,

679
00:35:46,687 --> 00:35:49,606
which it tries to hide
behind some sort of grandeur.

680
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:54,862
That's the design, Gem!

681
00:35:56,071 --> 00:35:58,365
There is beauty in imperfections

682
00:35:59,324 --> 00:36:00,409
and ruin.

683
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:02,286
Sorry, but I don't like it, Mama.

684
00:36:02,369 --> 00:36:05,038
There's one thing
you have to apologize for,

685
00:36:05,122 --> 00:36:06,081
and it's not this.

686
00:36:06,665 --> 00:36:08,792
Is it about the US thing?

687
00:36:08,876 --> 00:36:10,043
Are we doing this again?

688
00:36:10,127 --> 00:36:11,837
Yes, and there's nothing I can do.

689
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,255
So, please,

690
00:36:13,338 --> 00:36:15,674
just don't rub it in.

691
00:36:15,757 --> 00:36:17,050
Please?

692
00:36:17,801 --> 00:36:20,596
Josie,
why are you just standing there?

693
00:36:20,679 --> 00:36:23,307
Where are the applicants?
What? Are you still adjusting?

694
00:36:23,390 --> 00:36:25,976
Why are you still acting
like you're new here?

695
00:36:26,059 --> 00:36:27,603
There's one outside, ma'am.

696
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:38,780
Um, hi, ma'am! Good afternoon.

697
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:40,866
Y-You're so beautiful, ma'am.

698
00:36:42,451 --> 00:36:43,619
Thank you.

699
00:36:46,204 --> 00:36:47,372
Well?

700
00:36:47,456 --> 00:36:48,874
Good afternoon.

701
00:36:48,957 --> 00:36:50,709
I'm Larajean Loyola.

702
00:36:50,792 --> 00:36:53,337
I tried to rehearse my spiel for today,

703
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:57,257
but I forgot everything when I came here

704
00:36:57,758 --> 00:37:02,512
because it's so beautiful!
The jewelry, the gems,

705
00:37:03,096 --> 00:37:04,556
and of course, you, ma'am.

706
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:07,643
Everything is so breathtaking.

707
00:37:07,726 --> 00:37:10,270
You are so beautiful.

708
00:37:11,563 --> 00:37:15,943
But honestly,
the reason I'm here today

709
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:17,986
is because I want to work here.

710
00:37:18,070 --> 00:37:20,447
I know it's a bit too high
for me to dream,

711
00:37:20,530 --> 00:37:22,783
but I don't think
there's anything wrong with that.

712
00:37:23,408 --> 00:37:27,245
And I believe I can get there
if I learn from the best.

713
00:37:27,329 --> 00:37:30,457
Well, being ambitious is a good start.

714
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:33,418
But then, what are your actual skills?

715
00:37:34,002 --> 00:37:35,712
Fix my schedule for tomorrow.

716
00:37:42,177 --> 00:37:44,596
I can see it's color-coded,

717
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:47,724
but it's not aligned
based on your priorities.

718
00:37:47,808 --> 00:37:51,269
If we move your 9 a.m. Zoom to 8:30,

719
00:37:51,353 --> 00:37:55,482
you'll have some buffer time
for the glam meeting at 10:00.

720
00:37:55,565 --> 00:37:59,069
I'll have them bring options
so you can make a quicker selection.

721
00:38:00,195 --> 00:38:04,116
And then, you have
a brunch sched with Raya.

722
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:06,368
We can do that at the same time
as your facial treatment,

723
00:38:06,451 --> 00:38:08,495
so you can go on a single trip instead.

724
00:38:08,578 --> 00:38:11,790
And for your 6 p.m. pictorial,
I'll clear everything before 4:00,

725
00:38:11,873 --> 00:38:14,167
so you can have a clear aura afterwards.

726
00:38:14,251 --> 00:38:17,379
Beauty, business, family, and play,

727
00:38:17,462 --> 00:38:18,839
in that order, ma'am.

728
00:38:23,301 --> 00:38:24,469
Thank you.

729
00:38:26,013 --> 00:38:26,972
We'll call you.

730
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:31,143
M-may I know when that is?
Even just an estimated time.

731
00:38:32,477 --> 00:38:34,479
Aside from being ambitious,

732
00:38:34,563 --> 00:38:37,024
there's something else
I expect of an employee,

733
00:38:37,858 --> 00:38:39,276
and that's having patience.

734
00:38:40,068 --> 00:38:41,653
Someone who can wait.

735
00:38:46,950 --> 00:38:49,202
- <i>Hello, sir?</i>
- Where are you?

736
00:38:49,286 --> 00:38:52,164
- I'm at home, sir.
- <i>Where's that?</i>

737
00:38:52,247 --> 00:38:53,665
I want to unwind.

738
00:38:54,249 --> 00:38:55,250
Let's have a drink.

739
00:38:56,793 --> 00:38:58,045
You know, Attorney...

740
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:04,843
My son here, he's carrying so much
on his back right now.

741
00:39:04,926 --> 00:39:08,055
That job that you gave him?

742
00:39:08,889 --> 00:39:10,140
That was a huge blessing for us.

743
00:39:10,223 --> 00:39:14,061
I hope we can find luck with you.

744
00:39:14,144 --> 00:39:15,854
That is, if he does his job well.

745
00:39:16,104 --> 00:39:17,439
Of course I will, sir.

746
00:39:17,522 --> 00:39:19,733
I have to give back to my family anyway.

747
00:39:19,816 --> 00:39:21,109
Give back?

748
00:39:21,193 --> 00:39:25,197
You're the one
who's sacrificed so much for us.

749
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:28,492
You know, Attorney,
ever since my accident,

750
00:39:29,076 --> 00:39:30,452
he's taken care of everything.

751
00:39:30,535 --> 00:39:35,499
He's become a parent
to his youngest sibling.

752
00:39:35,582 --> 00:39:36,917
I admit,

753
00:39:37,709 --> 00:39:39,044
he has been...

754
00:39:40,337 --> 00:39:43,799
a much more responsible parent
than I could ever be.

755
00:39:43,882 --> 00:39:45,675
It's not that, Pa.

756
00:39:46,259 --> 00:39:47,260
Don't worry.

757
00:39:47,344 --> 00:39:49,846
I'm going to fulfill
everything on your wish list.

758
00:39:49,930 --> 00:39:50,889
Like what?

759
00:39:50,972 --> 00:39:53,975
Well, for one, his prosthetic leg.

760
00:39:54,059 --> 00:39:56,853
I would also like to set up
our auto repair shop again.

761
00:39:56,937 --> 00:39:59,689
And also get our car wash business fixed.

762
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:03,026
And finally, to get our youngest
into a good school.

763
00:40:03,110 --> 00:40:05,487
And because I love your life story,

764
00:40:05,570 --> 00:40:08,031
I got it.

765
00:40:08,115 --> 00:40:09,282
Oh, sir, please don't.

766
00:40:09,366 --> 00:40:11,326
I can do it. I can work hard for it.

767
00:40:12,202 --> 00:40:14,538
I don't like being opposed.

768
00:40:14,621 --> 00:40:17,082
And I'm telling you,
I take everything personally.

769
00:40:19,543 --> 00:40:22,170
I can make my opponents shut up.

770
00:40:28,510 --> 00:40:30,720
Gotcha!

771
00:40:30,804 --> 00:40:32,639
I was just joking, you guys.

772
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:36,017
You almost gave me a heart attack there!

773
00:40:36,268 --> 00:40:38,061
- But Teo...
- He got us!

774
00:40:38,145 --> 00:40:40,605
But Teo, I'm serious about my offer.

775
00:40:40,689 --> 00:40:41,815
I got you.

776
00:40:41,898 --> 00:40:43,984
My family is my responsibility, sir.

777
00:40:44,818 --> 00:40:48,238
I can't accept anything
more than my salary.

778
00:40:48,864 --> 00:40:50,574
It's my form of self-respect.

779
00:40:51,158 --> 00:40:53,118
Self-respect or pride?

780
00:40:54,870 --> 00:40:56,037
Both!

781
00:40:56,121 --> 00:40:57,664
And believe me,
because of that,

782
00:40:57,747 --> 00:40:59,457
I admire you so much more.

783
00:41:00,375 --> 00:41:02,335
A man with dignity.

784
00:41:02,419 --> 00:41:03,587
That's rare these days.

785
00:41:04,004 --> 00:41:06,214
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

786
00:41:06,298 --> 00:41:07,549
Where are you taking me?

787
00:41:07,632 --> 00:41:09,259
You're going to pass out, Pa.

788
00:41:09,342 --> 00:41:11,469
Wait here, sir. Oops, careful!

789
00:41:11,553 --> 00:41:13,388
- You're so drunk.
- Attorney!

790
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:15,473
Wait there. I'll come back in a bit.

791
00:41:17,976 --> 00:41:19,477
- Stay there, okay?
- Okay.

792
00:41:22,939 --> 00:41:25,817
- You okay, sir?
- All good.

793
00:41:25,901 --> 00:41:27,402
Won't Ma'am Gem get mad at you?

794
00:41:27,485 --> 00:41:28,653
Will she?

795
00:41:28,737 --> 00:41:30,614
I love that woman.

796
00:41:31,531 --> 00:41:33,033
You're perfect for each other.

797
00:41:34,784 --> 00:41:36,453
Where did you meet anyway?

798
00:41:36,536 --> 00:41:38,371
I was on vacation in Spain.

799
00:41:40,874 --> 00:41:42,250
<i>I got too drunk.</i>

800
00:41:46,296 --> 00:41:47,505
And I got robbed.

801
00:41:51,009 --> 00:41:52,177
<i>- </i>That's mine!

802
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:54,012
And there she was when I opened my eyes.

803
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:02,479
<i>The angel who saved me.</i>

804
00:42:04,940 --> 00:42:07,817
And it turns out,
we were staying at the same hotel.

805
00:42:07,901 --> 00:42:09,903
We literally needed each other that night.

806
00:42:09,986 --> 00:42:11,404
Destiny.

807
00:42:11,488 --> 00:42:13,156
And the rest is history.

808
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:16,159
Could it have been planned?

809
00:42:16,826 --> 00:42:17,827
Maybe an M.O.?

810
00:42:17,911 --> 00:42:19,371
What do you mean?

811
00:42:19,454 --> 00:42:21,248
Some criminals do that.

812
00:42:21,331 --> 00:42:24,417
They'd take advantage of a drunk person.

813
00:42:24,501 --> 00:42:25,919
No, no, no, no.

814
00:42:26,378 --> 00:42:27,879
Gem is a very kind person.

815
00:42:31,091 --> 00:42:32,801
What else did you like about her?

816
00:42:32,884 --> 00:42:34,135
Everything.

817
00:42:34,469 --> 00:42:35,762
She has a good heart.

818
00:42:35,845 --> 00:42:37,806
She's well-off but grounded.

819
00:42:37,889 --> 00:42:39,975
Decent. Refined.

820
00:42:40,058 --> 00:42:42,811
She has a heart for the poor,
and she does not judge.

821
00:42:43,478 --> 00:42:44,980
She was brought up
with love by her parents,

822
00:42:45,063 --> 00:42:47,065
so she had a good upbringing.

823
00:42:48,066 --> 00:42:51,361
Speaking of, where were they
on Ma'am Gem's birthday?

824
00:42:51,444 --> 00:42:53,571
Mm! They're in Spain.

825
00:42:53,822 --> 00:42:54,990
Señor Jorge,

826
00:42:55,407 --> 00:42:58,243
her father, is the biggest wine importer
to the Philippines.

827
00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:00,912
<i>Viña del Marques Importaciones.</i>

828
00:43:00,996 --> 00:43:03,331
And her mother, Adriana,
is a socialite.

829
00:43:03,415 --> 00:43:05,208
She was sick, so she couldn't go.

830
00:43:07,669 --> 00:43:08,920
What about you, Teo?

831
00:43:09,629 --> 00:43:11,047
Do you have a wife,

832
00:43:11,131 --> 00:43:12,716
- a girlfriend?
- He's single!

833
00:43:12,799 --> 00:43:14,968
But he had a girlfriend!

834
00:43:15,051 --> 00:43:16,469
Pa, go to sleep!

835
00:43:18,471 --> 00:43:19,931
The woman who looks like my wife?

836
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:21,933
No, sir.

837
00:43:22,517 --> 00:43:24,060
Not even a little bit.

838
00:43:24,644 --> 00:43:26,062
Even her personality is different.

839
00:43:26,146 --> 00:43:28,273
My ex was evil.

840
00:43:30,025 --> 00:43:31,151
You sound bitter.

841
00:43:31,776 --> 00:43:33,028
Was it a bad breakup?

842
00:43:34,654 --> 00:43:35,572
Yeah.

843
00:43:36,990 --> 00:43:40,118
She made a fool out of me big time.

844
00:43:41,536 --> 00:43:43,538
She pulled me into her hell.

845
00:43:44,039 --> 00:43:45,165
Turns out, she's a criminal.

846
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:46,583
So, yeah.

847
00:43:47,334 --> 00:43:49,377
She dragged me into her sins.

848
00:43:49,961 --> 00:43:52,172
Well, she's for sure
paying for her sins now.

849
00:43:52,255 --> 00:43:55,091
She's probably burning
in wherever hell she may be.

850
00:43:57,510 --> 00:43:58,470
Cheers.

851
00:44:00,347 --> 00:44:01,306
Cheers, sir.

852
00:44:30,543 --> 00:44:32,170
- Teo?
- Hmm?

853
00:44:32,253 --> 00:44:33,713
Are you busy?

854
00:44:33,797 --> 00:44:35,006
A bit.

855
00:44:35,090 --> 00:44:36,925
But for you, no.

856
00:44:38,218 --> 00:44:40,011
I'm going to take remedial classes,

857
00:44:40,095 --> 00:44:42,263
so I can catch up
with the rest of the batch.

858
00:44:42,347 --> 00:44:44,599
- Mm-hmm.
- And so I can enroll next year.

859
00:44:44,682 --> 00:44:48,478
I also have a competency exam coming up.

860
00:44:48,561 --> 00:44:51,064
Here are my notes.

861
00:44:51,981 --> 00:44:54,317
I got 100% on the mock test!

862
00:44:54,401 --> 00:44:57,487
Wow! You're smart just like me!

863
00:44:57,570 --> 00:44:59,322
Of course, Teo!

864
00:44:59,406 --> 00:45:00,615
Now, wait a minute.

865
00:45:00,698 --> 00:45:02,909
I heard that.

866
00:45:02,992 --> 00:45:04,077
Fine.

867
00:45:05,412 --> 00:45:07,205
I guess you inherited my good manners.

868
00:45:08,456 --> 00:45:12,961
If you pass all of the tests,
you'll be able to go back to school soon.

869
00:45:13,044 --> 00:45:14,879
Thank you, Teo!

870
00:45:14,963 --> 00:45:16,881
Do you already have money for my tuition?

871
00:45:16,965 --> 00:45:18,758
I will, very soon!

872
00:45:18,842 --> 00:45:20,135
But we'll have to pay
in installments, okay?

873
00:45:20,218 --> 00:45:23,138
- Thanks again, Teo!
- You're welcome. Go on.

874
00:45:23,888 --> 00:45:25,682
- Hey, Pa. Hmm?
- Son?

875
00:45:25,765 --> 00:45:29,686
Your boss's assistant, Eric, called.

876
00:45:29,769 --> 00:45:32,147
It turns out your boss was serious

877
00:45:32,230 --> 00:45:34,607
about his offer
to get me a prosthetic leg.

878
00:45:34,691 --> 00:45:36,192
They want to get my measurements already.

879
00:45:36,276 --> 00:45:38,069
But I already turned down Sir Ace's offer.

880
00:45:38,153 --> 00:45:39,988
Then just politely decline again
and thank him.

881
00:45:41,489 --> 00:45:42,866
Okay, Pa.

882
00:46:10,643 --> 00:46:11,895
Mateo.

883
00:46:11,978 --> 00:46:13,563
- Judge.
- Can I have a word?

884
00:46:13,646 --> 00:46:15,940
Of course, Judge.
What can I do for you?

885
00:46:16,024 --> 00:46:18,359
Did you accompany Ace last night?

886
00:46:19,486 --> 00:46:20,612
He had a couple of drinks with us...

887
00:46:20,695 --> 00:46:22,447
No, before that.

888
00:46:22,530 --> 00:46:24,824
We took the car out for a test drive.

889
00:46:24,908 --> 00:46:27,535
Did you notice
anything different about Ace?

890
00:46:27,619 --> 00:46:29,162
Something off?

891
00:46:29,245 --> 00:46:31,456
Something... weird?

892
00:46:32,290 --> 00:46:33,333
No, Judge.

893
00:46:34,501 --> 00:46:35,668
He seemed tired.

894
00:46:36,794 --> 00:46:37,837
Teo.

895
00:46:38,505 --> 00:46:39,464
Judge.

896
00:46:40,215 --> 00:46:44,260
Ace told me you worked abroad. Where?

897
00:46:44,344 --> 00:46:45,762
In Morocco.

898
00:46:45,845 --> 00:46:46,846
Morocco?

899
00:46:48,556 --> 00:46:49,933
I see.

900
00:46:51,142 --> 00:46:52,560
That's all, Mateo.

901
00:46:53,144 --> 00:46:54,562
All right, Judge.

902
00:47:04,364 --> 00:47:08,326
Brother, I need you to check
someone's record for me.

903
00:47:09,744 --> 00:47:11,246
A background check.

904
00:47:23,216 --> 00:47:24,926
There is paid parking in the back

905
00:47:25,009 --> 00:47:28,179
for rich and privileged people like you,

906
00:47:28,263 --> 00:47:29,847
you entitled brat!

907
00:47:29,931 --> 00:47:31,391
- Stop! Don't you dare--
- Raya!

908
00:47:31,474 --> 00:47:32,976
- Stop!
- Girl, stop it!

909
00:47:33,059 --> 00:47:34,185
Hey!

910
00:47:34,269 --> 00:47:35,853
You've got some nerve!

911
00:47:35,937 --> 00:47:38,273
- Excuse me?
- Just ignore her.

912
00:47:38,356 --> 00:47:40,024
- Ouch!
- Janice!

913
00:47:41,943 --> 00:47:42,986
Relax, relax!

914
00:47:43,069 --> 00:47:44,487
- How dare you!
- Enough!

915
00:47:44,571 --> 00:47:46,739
This is unacceptable behavior!

916
00:47:46,823 --> 00:47:49,867
You should suspend her for it!

917
00:47:49,951 --> 00:47:51,119
You started it.

918
00:47:51,202 --> 00:47:52,537
Silence!

919
00:47:52,620 --> 00:47:53,705
You saw the incident?

920
00:47:54,497 --> 00:47:55,415
Yes, ma'am.

921
00:47:56,749 --> 00:48:00,587
She was blocking
the parking space to reserve it.

922
00:48:00,670 --> 00:48:04,465
She also instigated the fight.

923
00:48:04,549 --> 00:48:06,926
No! She was going to run over me!

924
00:48:07,010 --> 00:48:09,220
Because you refused to get out of the way!

925
00:48:09,304 --> 00:48:10,680
What are you? A human cone?

926
00:48:10,763 --> 00:48:13,975
Ms. Mendoza,
I want you to take a good look at this.

927
00:48:19,105 --> 00:48:20,106
Ms. Verona,

928
00:48:20,189 --> 00:48:22,400
if this incident happens again,

929
00:48:22,483 --> 00:48:24,402
don't take the matter into your own hands.

930
00:48:24,485 --> 00:48:26,195
Call our security guards.

931
00:48:27,488 --> 00:48:29,324
All of you, you may go.

932
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:32,702
Except for you, Ms. Mendoza! Stay!

933
00:48:33,328 --> 00:48:34,954
So sad.

934
00:48:36,497 --> 00:48:38,666
Miss! Excuse me.

935
00:48:40,001 --> 00:48:41,711
I'm Ronnie, by the way.

936
00:48:48,593 --> 00:48:49,761
Uh, miss?

937
00:48:49,844 --> 00:48:51,429
What's up with your friend?

938
00:48:51,512 --> 00:48:52,889
She didn't even say thank you.

939
00:48:52,972 --> 00:48:55,183
Yeah, she's like that.
But thank you for helping us back there.

940
00:48:55,266 --> 00:48:57,435
Hey, Raya! Wait for me!

941
00:49:00,563 --> 00:49:04,776
So, 5:45 p.m. in Pasig,
to meet with Mr. and Mrs. Reyes, and...

942
00:49:04,859 --> 00:49:06,653
Yeah, that's your schedule
for tomorrow, sir.

943
00:49:06,736 --> 00:49:08,488
All right. I better head home then.

944
00:49:09,113 --> 00:49:10,073
Sir.

945
00:49:11,449 --> 00:49:13,534
You left something in the car.

946
00:49:14,410 --> 00:49:15,620
I held onto it for safekeeping.

947
00:49:21,793 --> 00:49:23,628
Eric called Papa last night.

948
00:49:24,504 --> 00:49:25,672
Thank you, sir.

949
00:49:25,755 --> 00:49:28,299
But like I said,
I'll take care of Papa's prosthetic leg.

950
00:49:29,342 --> 00:49:30,468
I like you.

951
00:49:30,551 --> 00:49:32,387
You are not an opportunist.

952
00:49:32,470 --> 00:49:33,680
I hope you don't change.

953
00:49:33,763 --> 00:49:35,765
This is who I really am, sir.

954
00:49:36,974 --> 00:49:38,559
But thank you for everything.

955
00:49:38,643 --> 00:49:41,646
If you need anything else,
just let me know.

956
00:49:42,105 --> 00:49:43,147
We'll help you, okay?

957
00:49:44,273 --> 00:49:45,858
By the way,
what happened to his leg?

958
00:49:45,942 --> 00:49:47,568
It was an accident at the workshop.

959
00:49:47,652 --> 00:49:50,905
But even though he's down a leg,
Papa is still a great mechanic.

960
00:49:50,988 --> 00:49:53,157
He was a master mechanic back in Japan.

961
00:49:53,241 --> 00:49:55,159
He taught me everything I know.

962
00:49:55,243 --> 00:49:56,994
- Really?
- Yes, sir.

963
00:49:57,870 --> 00:50:00,832
When you get busy driving,
I can hire him to help out.

964
00:50:01,791 --> 00:50:03,918
Let's talk about it
when we get back from our trip, okay?

965
00:50:04,001 --> 00:50:05,169
Thank you, sir.

966
00:50:08,005 --> 00:50:09,090
Hello, love?

967
00:50:11,801 --> 00:50:14,637
So, Jorge, how is Adriana?

968
00:50:15,555 --> 00:50:17,223
She's doing good.

969
00:50:17,765 --> 00:50:20,935
She wants to come,
but she needs to recover first.

970
00:50:21,018 --> 00:50:21,853
Mm.

971
00:50:21,936 --> 00:50:24,480
I hope
she responds well to the treatment.

972
00:50:25,565 --> 00:50:26,607
Raya.

973
00:50:26,691 --> 00:50:29,694
Didn't I tell you,
no gadgets on the table?

974
00:50:29,777 --> 00:50:30,987
I'm sorry, Ma.

975
00:50:31,070 --> 00:50:32,780
I was just absorbed with this.

976
00:50:32,864 --> 00:50:35,366
About what?

977
00:50:35,450 --> 00:50:37,160
About what?

978
00:50:37,243 --> 00:50:39,120
A woman named Daniela Ordonez

979
00:50:39,203 --> 00:50:41,080
was arrested by authorities.

980
00:50:42,165 --> 00:50:45,668
Wanted for
human smuggling, illegal recruitment,

981
00:50:45,752 --> 00:50:47,587
and she was also the one

982
00:50:47,670 --> 00:50:52,175
who allegedly recruited
the OFW who died recently.

983
00:50:52,592 --> 00:50:54,844
The one who fell
from a building in Morocco.

984
00:50:56,179 --> 00:50:59,432
I don't think
that's appropriate table conversation.

985
00:51:02,518 --> 00:51:04,187
Here is Daniela Ordonez.

986
00:51:07,356 --> 00:51:08,191
Sir?

987
00:51:08,274 --> 00:51:10,943
<i>I'm sorry, sir. I got caught.</i>

988
00:51:11,027 --> 00:51:14,405
<i>Sir, my husband and my family need me.</i>

989
00:51:14,489 --> 00:51:16,949
<i>I followed our system.</i>

990
00:51:17,033 --> 00:51:19,994
Someone must've tipped off
the authorities.

991
00:51:20,077 --> 00:51:21,746
Sir, I'm really sorry.

992
00:51:21,829 --> 00:51:23,164
<i>Please help me, sir.</i>

993
00:51:24,791 --> 00:51:26,125
Wait there.

994
00:51:26,209 --> 00:51:28,795
<i>Do not speak to anyone.</i>

995
00:51:28,878 --> 00:51:30,087
I'll help you.

996
00:51:31,214 --> 00:51:33,007
As I always do.

997
00:51:33,090 --> 00:51:35,843
Okay, Judge. Thank you.

998
00:51:45,019 --> 00:51:46,437
Brother!

999
00:51:46,771 --> 00:51:49,065
I found something on my social media.

1000
00:51:49,398 --> 00:51:52,360
Remember that picnic we had
with that girl I was dating before?

1001
00:51:52,443 --> 00:51:53,277
Mm.

1002
00:51:53,361 --> 00:51:55,738
A picture was saved on my phone.

1003
00:51:56,030 --> 00:51:58,699
Good thing onecloudsky was invented.

1004
00:51:58,783 --> 00:52:00,076
<i>It saved everything,</i>

1005
00:52:00,618 --> 00:52:02,703
except my money.

1006
00:52:02,787 --> 00:52:05,122
All right, send me the pic, Jepoy.

1007
00:52:07,041 --> 00:52:09,126
That'll be a big help.

1008
00:52:20,596 --> 00:52:22,974
Ma'am? Are you in a hurry?

1009
00:52:25,184 --> 00:52:26,894
I have to get something at the shop.

1010
00:52:26,978 --> 00:52:27,979
Traffic's really heavy getting there.

1011
00:52:28,062 --> 00:52:30,606
Perfect timing, I just finished
checking the car engines.

1012
00:52:30,690 --> 00:52:32,024
I can drop you off if you want.

1013
00:52:32,108 --> 00:52:33,192
Good idea.

1014
00:52:33,276 --> 00:52:35,278
Ace isn't leaving today anyway.

1015
00:52:35,361 --> 00:52:37,196
Can we go now? I don't want to be late.

1016
00:52:50,626 --> 00:52:54,297
Ma'am, sorry to intrude,

1017
00:52:54,380 --> 00:52:56,424
but I have something to show you.

1018
00:52:56,507 --> 00:52:57,717
What's that?

1019
00:53:05,850 --> 00:53:07,685
I see the resemblance.

1020
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:10,855
She's pretty.

1021
00:53:11,981 --> 00:53:13,316
Where is she now?

1022
00:53:16,944 --> 00:53:17,987
She died, ma'am.

1023
00:53:19,363 --> 00:53:20,698
Sorry to hear that.

1024
00:53:22,366 --> 00:53:23,910
You don't have to apologize, ma'am.

1025
00:53:23,993 --> 00:53:26,120
She was a terrible person.

1026
00:53:26,203 --> 00:53:27,246
The worst.

1027
00:53:27,330 --> 00:53:29,081
I despise her, ma'am.

1028
00:53:29,165 --> 00:53:31,542
If that's true,

1029
00:53:32,293 --> 00:53:36,005
you should get rid of
all your memories of her.

1030
00:53:36,088 --> 00:53:37,548
You should burn that photo

1031
00:53:37,632 --> 00:53:39,467
along with all of your memories together.

1032
00:53:39,550 --> 00:53:44,722
I'm sure her soul is already
burning in hell, ma'am.

1033
00:53:44,805 --> 00:53:45,848
That's good.

1034
00:53:45,932 --> 00:53:47,808
Whatever's good for your mental health,

1035
00:53:47,892 --> 00:53:49,060
do it.

1036
00:53:49,143 --> 00:53:51,395
Teo, life is short.

1037
00:53:51,479 --> 00:53:54,231
You should just be happy. Move on.

1038
00:54:02,406 --> 00:54:04,909
What the hell?

1039
00:54:04,992 --> 00:54:07,161
I'm sorry, ma'am.
Someone crossed the road.

1040
00:54:09,080 --> 00:54:12,667
Look, if you can't do your job properly,

1041
00:54:12,750 --> 00:54:14,293
you should just resign.

1042
00:54:15,419 --> 00:54:17,088
I'm sorry, ma'am.

1043
00:54:52,164 --> 00:54:53,666
What are you doing here?

1044
00:54:54,625 --> 00:54:56,002
I applied...

1045
00:54:56,085 --> 00:54:58,045
and got hired! Surprise!

1046
00:54:58,337 --> 00:54:59,547
Didn't I tell you not to?

1047
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:01,799
Unbelievable.

1048
00:55:01,882 --> 00:55:05,511
If they find out we know each other,
we could lose our jobs.

1049
00:55:05,594 --> 00:55:08,389
And if they find out I went to jail,
you'll be in trouble too.

1050
00:55:08,472 --> 00:55:10,683
You didn't tell them you went to jail?

1051
00:55:10,766 --> 00:55:13,436
No, because it happened overseas.

1052
00:55:13,519 --> 00:55:16,605
And the physical assault charges
were dropped anyway.

1053
00:55:17,773 --> 00:55:20,568
Just do me a favor. Don't let anyone know.

1054
00:55:20,651 --> 00:55:22,486
You keep asking me for favors.

1055
00:55:22,570 --> 00:55:25,656
You owe me big time. Go on.

1056
00:55:33,873 --> 00:55:35,082
Hi, ma'am.

1057
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:39,253
Miss Gem, meet Larajean,

1058
00:55:39,336 --> 00:55:42,006
the new assistant to the assistant.

1059
00:55:42,089 --> 00:55:43,424
You made the cut.

1060
00:55:44,675 --> 00:55:46,761
I guess Mama has someone new to torment.

1061
00:55:46,844 --> 00:55:50,473
By the way, tell Mama that
I'm leaving for the airport in an hour.

1062
00:55:50,556 --> 00:55:52,016
Yes, ma'am.

1063
00:55:53,267 --> 00:55:54,268
Hey.

1064
00:55:57,855 --> 00:55:59,690
I will miss you.

1065
00:56:00,024 --> 00:56:01,358
Me too, Papa.

1066
00:56:04,361 --> 00:56:06,322
And you take care of Mama, okay?

1067
00:56:06,405 --> 00:56:07,740
And this is for Mama.

1068
00:56:07,823 --> 00:56:12,119
I made this especially for her.

1069
00:56:12,203 --> 00:56:13,454
She will love it.

1070
00:56:15,539 --> 00:56:17,875
You two, stay in love.

1071
00:56:17,958 --> 00:56:20,878
Always talk things out.

1072
00:56:20,961 --> 00:56:21,796
Yes, Papa,

1073
00:56:21,879 --> 00:56:23,798
and I'm sorry
I can't bring you to the airport today.

1074
00:56:23,881 --> 00:56:25,883
- No problem.
- Take care.

1075
00:56:25,966 --> 00:56:28,094
Shall we?
You'll be okay, love?

1076
00:56:28,177 --> 00:56:31,097
If there's a problem,
just text me or give me a call, okay?

1077
00:56:31,180 --> 00:56:32,014
Okay.

1078
00:56:32,098 --> 00:56:33,682
- I love you.
- I love you.

1079
00:56:36,769 --> 00:56:37,770
Take care.

1080
00:57:51,135 --> 00:57:52,386
What are you doing here?

1081
00:57:52,469 --> 00:57:53,596
Uh...

1082
00:57:53,679 --> 00:57:55,598
I just returned something
to the storage room.

1083
00:57:55,681 --> 00:57:57,141
I'm heading home already, ma'am.

1084
00:58:16,285 --> 00:58:17,995
You can go home.

1085
00:58:18,078 --> 00:58:18,996
Yes, ma'am.

1086
00:58:21,207 --> 00:58:22,958
- Oh... ouch!
- Ma'am!

1087
00:58:23,959 --> 00:58:24,960
Are you okay?

1088
00:58:29,173 --> 00:58:30,257
Are you hurt?

1089
00:58:31,383 --> 00:58:33,052
What the hell is going on?

1090
00:58:36,305 --> 00:58:38,641
Babe... Ace! Ace, stop!

1091
00:58:38,724 --> 00:58:40,392
- What's going on?
- Ace!

1092
00:58:40,476 --> 00:58:41,310
- Guards!
- Mama!

1093
00:58:41,393 --> 00:58:43,395
Ace! Stop it! Stop it!

1094
00:58:43,479 --> 00:58:45,397
You're fired! Get him out of here!

1095
00:58:50,236 --> 00:58:51,737
- What's going on?
- What happened?

1096
00:58:51,820 --> 00:58:53,697
Teo was just...
Ace, let me explain!

1097
00:58:54,323 --> 00:58:55,241
Ace!

1098
00:58:55,324 --> 00:58:56,617
Ow! You're hurting me!

1099
00:58:56,700 --> 00:58:58,244
Ace, stop it!

1100
00:58:58,327 --> 00:59:01,163
- Please!
- Ace, please! Ace!

1101
00:59:02,998 --> 00:59:04,166
- What was that?
- Ace!

1102
00:59:04,250 --> 00:59:05,167
Admit it!

1103
00:59:05,251 --> 00:59:06,543
- Ace!
- No!

1104
00:59:06,627 --> 00:59:09,004
There's nothing going on!

1105
00:59:10,756 --> 00:59:12,132
<i>He's a convict!</i>

1106
00:59:12,216 --> 00:59:14,635
<i>As if we don't employ people</i>
<i>with criminal records.</i>

1107
00:59:14,718 --> 00:59:15,886
<i>Maybe we could use him.</i>

1108
00:59:15,970 --> 00:59:17,471
What else are you hiding from me?

1109
00:59:17,554 --> 00:59:19,139
<i>You're hanging by a thin rope.</i>

1110
00:59:19,223 --> 00:59:20,307
One mistake and you're done.

1111
00:59:20,391 --> 00:59:22,851
Your plan smells like vengeance

1112
00:59:22,935 --> 00:59:25,312
with karma on the side to me, Teo.

1113
00:59:25,396 --> 00:59:28,065
I don't want revenge, I want justice.

1114
00:59:28,148 --> 00:59:30,067
<i>You were a fake then,</i>
<i>you're an even bigger fake now!</i>

1115
00:59:30,150 --> 00:59:31,527
I am not that woman!

1116
00:59:31,610 --> 00:59:33,237
Drop the act, Yana!

1117
00:59:33,320 --> 00:59:34,655
Help! Ace!

1118
00:59:34,738 --> 00:59:37,324
You have no idea
how much pain you caused me!
